      <body>
         <msDesc>
            <msIdentifier>
               <msName xml:lang="en" type="general">prayer book</msName>
               <country>United Kingdom</country>
               <settlement>London</settlement>
               <repository>British Library</repository>
               <collection>Additional manuscripts</collection>
               <idno type="shelfmark">Add. MS 8245</idno>
               <altIdentifier type="catalgue">
                  <idno type="catalogue">52</idno>
                  <note>
                     <ref type="bibl" target="bib:Cleminson1988">Cleminson 1988: 66-67.</ref>
                  </note>
               </altIdentifier>
            </msIdentifier>
            <physDesc>
               <objectDesc form="codex">
                  <supportDesc>
                     <support>
                        <material>Paper
                        </material>
                        <watermark>
                           <motif>Arms of Amsterdam</motif>
                           <term>with some resemblance to</term>
                           <ref type="bibl" target="bib:Churchill1935">
                              <num>35</num>
                              <date>1698</date>
                              <num>41</num>
                              <date>1706</date>
                           </ref>
                        </watermark>
                     </support>
                     <extent>
                        <measure unit="folia">i+i+90+i</measure>
                        <dimensions unit="mm" type="folia" scope="f.1-91">
                           <height>155</height>
                           <width>95</width>
                        </dimensions>
                        <dimensions type="written" unit="mm" scope="f.1-91">
                           <height>120</height>
                           <width>65</width>
                        </dimensions>
                     </extent>
                     <foliation>
                        <date>Modern.</date>
                        <signatures>i, (ia, ib), 2-87, (88-91). Previous foliation: 1-86, on ff. 2-87.</signatures>
                     </foliation>
                     <collation>
                        <summary>Indeterminable because of the stiffness of the binding</summary>
                        <catchwords>Catchword on each page</catchwords>
                        <ruling>15 single ruled ll./p.</ruling>
                     </collation>
                  </supportDesc>
                  <layoutDesc>
                     <layout columns="1" writtenLines="15" ruledLines="15"/>
                  </layoutDesc>
               </objectDesc>
               <ink>Black.</ink>
               <decoDesc>
                  <decoNote type="overview">Modest but very delicate ornamentation; ornamented black initials in geomtric style, some of them with floral motifs, in the titles and in the beginning of each article: ff. <locus>2</locus>,
              <locus>14</locus>, <locus>37v</locus>, <locus>49</locus>, <locus>60</locus>, <locus>80</locus>.</decoNote>
               </decoDesc>
               <bindingDesc>
                  <p>Heavily restored, black leather on card, a gold saltire front and back, <dimensions unit="mm" type="binding">
                        <height>160</height>
                        <width>100</width>
                     </dimensions>. The leather from the older binding with simple blind tooled borders and floral ornaments is re-used for both covers; page-edges are gilded.</p>
               </bindingDesc>
               <additions type="inscriptions">
                  <list type="simple">
                     <item>
                        <locus>f. i a</locus>
                        <quote xml:lang="en" defective="false">
                           <persName type="owner" full="yes">John Meetchewrin</persName>
                           <date>1717</date> My <persName type="owner" full="yes">Lord Apraxin</persName>s Gift</quote>
                     </item>
                     <item>
                        <locus>f. 87v</locus>
                        <date>17th/18th c.</date>
                        <quote xml:lang="cu" defective="false">
                         сиꙗ книга <name type="owner" full="yes">алеѯан<seg rend="sup">д</seg>ръ петровича оп'раѯина</name> ді, мо<seg rend="sup">с</seg>ковскогѡ пи<seg rend="sup">с</seg>ма
                        </quote>
                        <note>in skoropis'</note>
                     </item>
                     <item>
                        <locus>back pastedown</locus>
                        <quote type="inscription" xml:lang="en" defective="false">D+</quote>
                     </item>
                  </list>
               </additions>
            </physDesc>
            <scribeDesc>
               <scribe>
                  <locusGrp>
                     <locus>ff. 1-(91)</locus>
                  </locusGrp>
                  <name type="scribe" xml:id="AnonymousAdd8245BL" full="yes">anonymous</name>
                  <scriptDesc script="cyrs" type="cursive">
                     <p>A very late <hi>skoropis'</hi>, or detached cursive (<dim>3</dim>mm line, <dim>6</dim> mm between lines), with
              relatively few superscripts.</p>
                  </scriptDesc>
                  <scribeLang>
                     <orthography>
                        <p>Russian.</p>
                     </orthography>
                  </scribeLang>
                  <note>
                     <ref type="bibl" target="bib:Cleminson1988">Cleminson 1988: 66-67</ref>
                  </note>
               </scribe>
            </scribeDesc>
            <msContents defective="false">
               <summary>Provides a separate lamentation for each day of the week.</summary>
               <author cert="ascribed">Ephrem the Syrian</author>
               <sampleText xml:lang="cu">
                  <head xml:lang="cu">
                     <foreign xml:lang="cu">МОЛИТВЫ собранныи оⷮ б҃жествеⷩнаго писанїꙗ, множайшїиже оⷮ
              с҃тагѡ еѳрама. хотꙗщимъ опоⷧчатїсꙗ насвое еже постраⷭтеⷨ. ислас'темъ належащее п'роиⷥволенїе. </foreign>
                  </head>
               </sampleText>
               <msItemStruct xml:id="ACD1" type="translation" defective="false">
                  <locus n="1">2-13v</locus>
                  <title xml:lang="bg">Молитва за понеделник вечер</title>
                  <sampleText xml:lang="cu">
                     <head>П'лачь в'понедѣлоⷦ в'вечеⷬ.</head>
                     <incipit defective="false">Прїими м҃лнїе ск'верныхъ инечистыхъ устъ</incipit>
                  </sampleText>
               </msItemStruct>
               <msItemStruct xml:id="ACD2" type="translation" defective="false">
                  <locus n="2">14-25</locus>
                  <title xml:lang="bg">Молитва за вторник вечер</title>
                  <sampleText xml:lang="cu">
                     <head>Плачь вовтороⷦ вечеръ;</head>
                     <incipit defective="false">Ꙋвы мнѣ, в'коеⷨ зазорѣ свою; вкоемъ студѣ воз'лежу</incipit>
                  </sampleText>
               </msItemStruct>
               <msItemStruct xml:id="ACD3" type="translation" defective="false">
                  <locus n="3">25v-37</locus>
                  <title xml:lang="bg">Молитва за сряда вечер</title>
                  <sampleText xml:lang="cu">
                     <head>Плачь в'среду в'вечеръ.</head>
                     <incipit defective="false">Трудъ г҃лати коб҃гу понуⷤдаеⷮмꙗ. недоствоже мое</incipit>
                  </sampleText>
               </msItemStruct>
               <msItemStruct xml:id="ACD4" type="translation" defective="false">
                  <locus n="4">37v-48v</locus>
                  <title xml:lang="bg">Молитва за четвъртък вечер</title>
                  <sampleText xml:lang="cu">
                     <head>Плачъ вчетвертокъ в'вечеръ.</head>
                     <incipit defective="false">Се пакꙗ п҃рипадаю д҃вереⷨ моего влⷣкꙗ</incipit>
                  </sampleText>
               </msItemStruct>
               <msItemStruct xml:id="ACD5" type="translation" defective="false">
                  <locus n="5">49-59v</locus>
                  <title xml:lang="bg">Молитва за петък вечер</title>
                  <author>Ephrem the Syrian</author>
                  <sampleText xml:lang="cu">
                     <head>Плачъ в'пꙗтокъ в'вечеръ.</head>
                     <incipit defective="false">Д҃ша прискорбнаꙗ п'риступаетъ к'тебѣ с҃тыꙗ̆ влⷣкѡ</incipit>
                  </sampleText>
               </msItemStruct>
               <msItemStruct xml:id="ACD6" type="translation" defective="false">
                  <locus n="6">60-72v</locus>
                  <title xml:lang="bg">Молитва за събота вечер, 1</title>
                  <sampleText xml:lang="cu">
                     <head>Плачъ всубботу в'вечеръ</head>
                     <incipit defective="false">Н҃не еще ид'несь срамлеⷩныⷨ лицемъ</incipit>
                  </sampleText>
               </msItemStruct>
               <msItemStruct xml:id="ACD7" type="translation" defective="false">
                  <locus n="7">73-87</locus>
                  <title xml:lang="bg">Молитва за събота вечер, 2</title>
                  <sampleText xml:lang="cu">
                     <rubric>Втойже д҃нь и часъ,</rubric>
                     <incipit defective="false">Блгⷣть т'воꙗ даетъ ми г҃лати к'тебѣ гⷭди.</incipit>
                  </sampleText>
               </msItemStruct>
            </msContents>
            <history>
               <origin evidence="de visu" resp="#DR">
                  <origDate>17th-18th c.</origDate>
                  <origPlace>Unknown; Russian origin</origPlace>
                  <ref type="bibl" target="bib:Cleminson1988">Cleminson 1988: 66-67</ref>
               </origin>
               <provenance>
                  <locus>Inside the front cover</locus> is the bookplate of the Hon. <persName type="owner" full="yes">Frederic North</persName>
            (later the fifth Earl of Gilford). On North, see <ref type="publication" target="bib:Partridge1975">Partridge
              (1975)</ref>. An <persName full="yes">Ivan Mičurin</persName> was in Britain in 1701-1714:
            see <ref type="publication" target="bib:Cross1980">Cross (1980): 147</ref>. Count
            <persName full="yes">Alexandr Petrovič Apraksin</persName> (c. 1690-1725) was here in
                  1709-1716: see <ref type="publication" target="bib:Cross1980">Cross (1980):
              152-153.</ref>
               </provenance>
               <acquisition>After the sale of Frederic North's book in 1830 the MS was bought by the British Museum; bears a British museum stamp.</acquisition>
            </history>
